          Man Utd will probably start with a 4-4-2; this seems to be the current preferred set up. I can't see why Moyes would choose Ashley Young over Kagawa. Kagawa would offer extra support up front with RVP and Rooney - as was the case on Tuesday night - all the action on valencias wing, allowing Kagawa inside. I think Kagawa could keep Toure quiet, slowing city down on the counter. City look good at the minute despite that 3-2 loss to Cardiff, and the nil apice draw to Stoke. They still play some good football in their opponents half and Deco looks the part. Rio Ferdinand looks weak at the minute, he has been turned more times than a merry-go-round this season leaving Vidic to clean up. Rio will struggle against the acceleration and speed of Aguaro and the form of Deco. Personally I think Utd have what it takes to get the win; however, they will have to play their best football to get all 3 points as (in my opinion) a City goal is almost certain. 2-1 united.
